ion\";s:120:\"Make the entire site available in AMP or pick specific post types and templates; you can also opt-out on per-post basis.\";}i:8;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-8.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:138:\"Plugin checks for AMP validity and will indicate when: no issues are found, new issues need review, or issues block AMP from being served.\";}i:9;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-9.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:125:\"The editor will surface validation issues during content authoring. The specific blocks with validation errors are indicated.\";}i:10;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-10.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:167:\"Each Validated URL shows the list of validation errors encountered, giving control over whether invalid markup is removed or kept. Keeping invalid markup disables AMP.\";}i:11;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:164:\"Each validation error provides a stack trace to identify which code is responsible for the invalid markup, whether a theme, plugin, embed, content block, and so on.\";}i:12;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:143:\"Styles added by themes and plugins are automatically concatenated, minified, and tree-shaken to try to keep the total under 75KB of inline CSS.\";}i:13;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-13.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:125:\"A WP-CLI command is provided to check the URLs on a site for AMP validity. Results are available in the admin for inspection.\";}}s:8:\"versions\";a:36:{s:3:\"0.2\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.2.zip\";s:3:\"0.3\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.zip\";s:5:\"0.3.1\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.1.zip\";s:5:\"0.3.2\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugi